summary: So in your naivety you decided that Era of amateur Whiterun retextures gone? HA! Here another one.
descriptionHtml:
[font=Arial]Wish to have time to learn texture creating, but for now this thing is the best i can do.[/font]

[font=Arial]I spend a month with tweaks on my 34gb texture collection.  [/font]
[font=Arial]Have tried all possible variations to make a poor but cozy feeling.[/font]
[font=Arial]I love Renthal's creations af, so [/font][font=Trebuchet MS][size=3]a-close-to[/size] [/font][font=Arial]style was a priority.[/font]
[font=Arial]Cant handle enb soo... its dark, i love how it looks.[/font]

[font=Comic Sans MS][size=1]Hope someone will make better screens with it.

[/size][/font]Most textures are 2k, rare 4k.

[font=Arial]Please make a [/font][font=Courier New][size=3]backup[/size][/font][font=Arial] of your Whiterun texture folder before installation.
(PST, there also [/font][font=Courier New]smim[/font][font=Arial] folder in my pack, use it with [/font][font=Verdana]SMIM[/font][font=Arial] mod, let it happen).
[/font]
[img]https://i.pinimg.com/originals/1d/7c/de/1d7cdedf8b5d04ec05f7872d6221eb79.jpg[/img]

ok now something new for a texture mod. None of this textures was created by me, literally, not even a single. This pack couldn't exist without original mods i've change with PainNET (And i highly recommend them) so---
